DigiLand — Agile Methodology
Property Registration System
Iterative Sprint-Based Development Lifecycle

Overview

DigiLand follows the Agile Methodology, it delivers the property registration system through multiple sprints. Each sprint has six phases namely: Plan, Design, Develop, Test, Deploy, and Review. This ensures a continuous delivery.
The core features are JWT authentication, SHA-256 property hashing, parallel data aggregation from DORIS/DLRC/CERSAI/MCA21, and Ethereum blockchain storage. They are built and validated more and more across sprints.

Agile Principles Applied to DigiLand

Iterative delivery:	Property registration features delivered sprint by sprint
Customer collaboration:	Stakeholder reviews after each sprint demo
Working software:	Each sprint produces testable API endpoints and UI
Respond to change:	New government API requirements added to backlog anytime
Continuous improvement:	Retrospectives improve team velocity each sprint
Self-organizing teams:	Dev team owns frontend, backend, and blockchain tasks
